 ecosystems, or communities. If your research fits into these criteria please answer following questions. As a default please fill the Horizon Europe - Ethics template, however other templates are available.</description></extraField></extraFields><referenceFields/><uploadFields/><descriptionTemplates><descriptionTemplate minMultiplicity="0" maxMultiplicity="1"><descriptionTemplateGroupId>489adb0f-109e-4a9b-a234-525982eb711f</descriptionTemplateGroupId><descriptionTemplateCode>he-ethics</descriptionTemplateCode><label>Horizon Europe - Ethics</label></descriptionTemplate></descriptionTemplates><prefillingSources/></section><section hasTemplates="true" prefillingSourcesEnabled="true" canEditDescriptionTemplates="true"><id>85f2eb1b-df89-45ab-93ff-da8bb015748a</id><label>Dataset descriptions</label><ordinal>3</ordinal><systemFields/><extraFields><extraField ordinal="1" required="false"><id>01543585-5161-4234-af3e-164d994b55f1</id><type>RichTex</type><label>Introduction</label><description>Please select a template to describe your dataset that best fits your research topic. You can chose more than one template. All the templates prepared for the AQUASERV project are called &amp;#34;AQUASERV | category | datatype&amp;#34;. If you can't find a template that fits your research, please contact aquaservhelpdesk@ualg.pt</description></extraField></extraFields><referenceFields/><uploadFields/><descriptionTemplates><descriptionTemplate><descriptionTemplateGroupId>e480ee0a-f234-4582-943c-ea5814279661</descriptionTemplateGroupId><descriptionTemplateCode>sequencing type</descriptionTemplateCode><label>AQUASERV | Molecular Biology &amp; Omics | sequencing</label></descriptionTemplate><descriptionTemplate><descriptionTemplateGroupId>76058eb5-3946-4af3-bb95-4ef46af0c442</descriptionTemplateGroupId><descriptionTemplateCode>AQUASERV generic</descriptionTemplateCode><label>AQUASERV | all categories | generic template</label></descriptionTemplate></descriptionTemplates><prefillingSources/></section></sections></definition><groupId>cbc4e985-0aba-4e82-998b-bbd9f1936611</groupId><description>This is the main AQUASERV blueprint containing common questions about you and your project, as well as multiple &amp;#34;templates.&amp;#34; The common questions need to be answered only once. Use one &amp;#34;template&amp;#34; for each dataset you are generating. For example, if you generate genomics data, use the genomics template (already available); if you generate LC-MS data, use the LC-MS template (coming soon). If you generate more than one type of dataset, you can combine multiple templates into one DMP &amp;#34;plan.&amp;#34;</description></blueprint><blueprintValues><blueprintValue><fieldId>f8d83ee7-6083-4f99-ae69-b61b029ca6f2</fieldId><value>Sample collection and processing complies with EU animal welfare&amp;#160;&lt;span&gt;regulations. Animal manipulation complies with the guidelines of the European Union Directive (2010/63/EU) and the Italian&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Legislative Decree 26 of March 4, 2014 &amp;#8220;Attuazione della Direttiva 2010/63/UE sulla protezione degli animali utilizzati a fini&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;scientifici&amp;#34;. As the proposal aims to address knowledge gaps in understanding miRNA functions in marine teleosts by focusing on&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;the European seabass,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;a species that is frequently challenged by lethal bacterial and viral infections, the work couldn't be carried out without conducting&amp;#160;&lt;span&gt;experiments or other scientific procedures on&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#160;living animals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</value></blueprintValue><blueprintValue><fieldId>01543585-5161-4234-af3e-164d994b55f1</fieldId><value>Description of the dataset to be generated within the miRBass project</value></blueprintValue></blueprintValues><descriptionTemplates><descriptionTemplate><descriptionTemplateGroupId>489adb0f-109e-4a9b-a234-525982eb711f</descript