esearch</label><reference>openorgs____::0000003103</reference><fieldId>f9b422c9-0b4b-434e-a034-856144515bb3</fieldId><type><id>7eeffb98-58fb-4921-82ec-e27f32f8e738</id><name>Organisations</name><code>organisations</code></type><source>openaire</source><sourceType>External</sourceType></reference></references><descriptions><description><id>2c195d92-f1b1-461b-9807-c80802a60f78</id><description>Sample collection and processing complies with EU animal welfare regulations. Animal manipulation complies with the guidelines of the European Union Directive (2010/63/EU) and the Italian Legislative Decree 26 of March 4, 2014 &amp;#8220;Attuazione della Direttiva 2010/63/UE sulla protezione degli animali utilizzati a fini scientifici&amp;#34;. As the proposal aims to address knowledge gaps in understanding miRNA functions in marine teleosts by focusing on the European seabass,&amp;#10;&lt;div&gt;a species that is frequently challenged by lethal bacterial and viral infections, the work couldn't be carried out without conducting experiments or other scientific procedures on living animals.&lt;/div&gt;</description><label>Ethics</label><status><id>c266e2ee-9ae9-4a2f-9b4b-bc6fb1dd54aa</id><name>Finalized</name></status><finalizedAt>2025-07-28T13:50:39.628932Z</finalizedAt><sectionId>6c61e9c0-6db1-42da-9842-ef23c4dafe97</sectionId><descriptionTemplate><id>ac6a60a1-a683-40ca-ab9c-3439bef7fd81</id><label>Horizon Europe - Ethics</label><code>he-ethics</code><description>A template of Horizon Europe about ethics.</description><language>en</language><type><id>eb733414-0e8c-46ba-a16b-01f9bb0e7a9f</id><code>ethics</code><name>Ethics</name></type><version>1</version><groupId>489adb0f-109e-4a9b-a234-525982eb711f</groupId><pages><page><id>bdf66fe5-7789-2f7f-e293-624d0a3c54ea</id><ordinal>0</ordinal><title>Ethics</title><sections><section><id>c46f5000-9acc-8a23-48a0-36878a7ace16</id><ordinal>0</ordinal><fieldSets><fieldSet><id>99299810-1a77-ac18-a55a-a38a763f1b96</id><ordinal>0</ordinal><field